{"tid":1638854,"cid":1,"subCid":0,"title":"政府：示威者等同恐怖份子","createTime":"2019-10-08T12:26:40.000Z","updateTime":"2019-10-08T13:04:08.000Z","uid":89754,"like":3,"dislike":3,"uniUserReply":15,"replies":[{"pid":"cb9f72c94ba5a51451db12c5f46c331b0a19f507","tid":1638854,"uid":89754,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2019-10-08T12:26:40.000Z","msg":"<strong>The violent actions of anti-government protesters in Hong Kong last week ticked all the boxes of &ldquo;terrorist acts&rdquo; as defined by international and local laws, multiple senior government sources told the Post.</strong><br />\nBut the administration has no plans to officially designate protesters as terrorists to avoid the devastating consequences such a decision could trigger.<br />\n&ldquo;It does not help the current situation and will cause public panic. We would also face an avalanche of consequences such as sanctions, disinvestment and a downgrade of credit rating. Our image would be torn up further.&rdquo;<br />\n<strong><br />\nThe sources pointed to Cap. 575 United Nations (Anti-Terrorism Measures) Ordinance, first enacted in Hong Kong in 2002 in line with a UN resolution after the September 11 terror attacks in the United States, that spells out terrorism related offences.</strong><br />\nThe section defines a &ldquo;terrorist act&rdquo; as an action that causes serious violence against a person, serious damage to property, endangers a person&rsquo;s life, creates a serious risk to the health or safety of the public, seriously interferes an electronic system, or seriously disrupts an essential service, facility or system.<br />\n<br />\n<a href=\"https://www.scmp.com/print/news/hong-kong/law-and-crime/article/3031895/we-cannot-tell-world-hong-kong-grooms-local-terrorists\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.scmp.com%2Fprint%2Fnews%2Fhong-kong%2Flaw-and-crime%2Farticle%2F3031895%2Fwe-cannot-tell-world-hong-kong-grooms-local-terrorists&d=NaStGCRJdOSKaO4BfYueNkngG4XMVyvHznkFIzn%2BcUY%3D&h=78ae7542\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.scmp.com/print/news/hong-kong/law-and-crime/article/3031895/we-cannot-tell-world-hong-kong-grooms-local-terrorists</a><br />\n人無恥便無敵<img src=\"/assets/faces/pig/mock.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/pig/mock.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/pig/mock.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"bf12729eaf880a39c0867fefd52e09b76e3b912c","tid":1638854,"uid":89754,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"quote":{"pid":"cb9f72c94ba5a51451db12c5f46c331b0a19f507","tid":1638854,"uid":89754,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2019-10-08T12:26:40.000Z","msg":"<strong>The violent actions of anti-government protesters in Hong Kong last week ticked all the boxes of &ldquo;terrorist acts&rdquo; as defined by international and local laws, multiple senior government sources told the Post.</strong><br />\nBut the administration has no plans to officially designate protesters as terrorists to avoid the devastating consequences such a decision could trigger.<br />\n&ldquo;It does not help the current situation and will cause public panic. We would also face an avalanche of consequences such as sanctions, disinvestment and a downgrade of credit rating. Our image would be torn up further.&rdquo;<br />\n<strong><br />\nThe sources pointed to Cap. 575 United Nations (Anti-Terrorism Measures) Ordinance, first enacted in Hong Kong in 2002 in line with a UN resolution after the September 11 terror attacks in the United States, that spells out terrorism related offences.</strong><br />\nThe section defines a &ldquo;terrorist act&rdquo; as an action that causes serious violence against a person, serious damage to property, endangers a person&rsquo;s life, creates a serious risk to the health or safety of the public, seriously interferes an electronic system, or seriously disrupts an essential service, facility or system.<br />\n<br />\n<a href=\"https://www.scmp.com/print/news/hong-kong/law-and-crime/article/3031895/we-cannot-tell-world-hong-kong-grooms-local-terrorists\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.scmp.com%2Fprint%2Fnews%2Fhong-kong%2Flaw-and-crime%2Farticle%2F3031895%2Fwe-cannot-tell-world-hong-kong-grooms-local-terrorists&d=NaStGCRJdOSKaO4BfYueNkngG4XMVyvHznkFIzn%2BcUY%3D&h=78ae7542\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.scmp.com/print/news/hong-kong/law-and-crime/article/3031895/we-cannot-tell-world-hong-kong-grooms-local-terrorists</a><br />\n人無恥便無敵<img src=\"/assets/faces/pig/mock.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/pig/mock.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/pig/mock.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-10-08T12:38:38.000Z","msg":"Push"},{"pid":"6dd0f4242c245d91a7e665cae912d9531442e85a","tid":1638854,"uid":212623,"like":3,"dislike":0,"score":3,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-10-08T12:39:32.000Z","msg":"又浮屍又跳樓呀無可疑邊個先係恐怖分子"},{"pid":"677aacdb745ffa72606740234a644d16a095ed5c","tid":1638854,"uid":103325,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-10-08T12:40:53.000Z","msg":"咁算唔算係定性為恐襲？"},{"pid":"d4c71c5920c2a89844b143f5eeee948a14ac13b1","tid":1638854,"uid":2607,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-10-08T12:43:41.000Z","msg":"<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/smile.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"3595e08dd6c70239f0e2dcc41d991253af095291","tid":1638854,"uid":225130,"like":1,"dislike":0,"score":1,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2019-10-08T12:44:20.000Z","msg":"屌你老母<br />\n前個的士佬係乜?"},{"pid":"28c89f84835a726188013355eb575e7af3cf798f","tid":1638854,"uid":225130,"like":2,"dislike":0,"score":2,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-10-08T12:44:48.000Z","msg":"依家一個警察都無死<br />\n<br />\n咁67暴動叫乜恐怖襲擊?"},{"pid":"fa79f092c1abbc925e0845fd0fae38954c4e3d7a","tid":1638854,"uid":219128,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"quote":{"pid":"3595e08dd6c70239f0e2dcc41d991253af095291","tid":1638854,"uid":225130,"like":1,"dislike":0,"score":1,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2019-10-0